   People at Work
   The Agency ISO 9001 Working Group is an informal working group made up
   of management representatives from across the agency who are directly
   responsible for maintaining certification at their respective NASA
   Center.

   The purpose of the working group is to collaborate on ideas, share
   lessons learned, and facilitate quality management practices and
   initiatives across the agency.

   Mr. Scott Holliday is the Program Manager for NASA's agency-wide ISO
   9001 initiatives. Mr. Holliday's office resides in the ISO 9001 Program
   Office (Code JI) in the Office of Management Systems located at NASA
   Headquarters.



